Quote:  <i>Mulesing</i>: Cutting off the wrinkles around the tail of Merino lambs with hand shears to reduce the risk of fly strike.
Notes:

Date:  1/3/2003
Source:  Listener (New Zealand Listener)
Author:
Vol / Page:  9
Edition:
Quote:  Merino sheep are also subjected to mulesing... The Merino breed has folds of skin around the breech that trap dags and thus predispose it to fly strike. During the mulesing procedure, up to six deep cuts are made in the buttocks to smooth out the skin surface.
